claim.claim-text:
10. A method of scanning objects by a scanner having a scanning table, comprising: 
a) conveying one or more objects to be scanned to the scanner using a conveyor mechanism; 
b) picking an object from the conveyor mechanism and mounting the object on the scanning table of the scanner; 
c) scanning the object; and 
d) removing the scanned object from the scanning table and delivering the scanned object to a discharge location.

16. A system for mass, automated scanning of dental study casts, comprising: 
a scanner having a scanning table; 
a plurality of cassettes, each said cassette having a maxilla and mandible study cast for a single patient mounted thereon in known positions relative to each another; 
a conveyor adjacent the scanner for delivering the cassettes to the scanner; and 
a pick and place mechanism engageable with said cassettes for picking one of said cassettes from said conveyor and mounting the picked cassette on said scanning table.
